        <!-- Romania -->
        <h2 id="romania" class="text-xl font-bold border-b border-gray-300 pb-1 mt-6 mb-3">Connection to Romania</h2>
        <p class="mb-3">
            Istrail has maintained strong ties to Romania throughout his career. He was awarded honorary citizenship by both his hometown of Târgu Neamț and the city of Iași, and received an honorary professorship from Alexandru Ioan Cuza University. He has given lectures and mentored students across Romanian universities and is featured in <em>Personalități de pe meridianul Ozana</em> (Personalities from the Ozana Meridian), a dictionary of notable figures from the Neamț region.
        </p>
        <p class="mb-3">
            He organized the long-running Solomon Marcus Guest Lecture Series at Brown, honoring the Romanian mathematician Solomon Marcus with twelve annual distinguished lectures spanning mathematics, linguistics, and the philosophy of science.
        </p>

